OL,6,F"Had that Act been in force at the
OL,7,Frelevant time for this case, between
OL,8,F(2021-23), I have no doubt that the
OL,9,Fprosecution would have proceeded to
OL,10,Ftrial."
OL,12,FFollowing the collapse of the trial,
OL,13,Fthe Crown Prosecution Service (CPS)
OL,14,Fpointed the finger at the government
OL,15,Fand its national security advisers,
OL,16,Fsaying evidence required to secure
OL,17,Fprosecution had not been forthcoming.
